cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on integrating AI into wireless networks, specifically cellular networks, and proposes a DRL-based scheduling solution. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses DRL, a subfield of machine learning, as the main approach for scheduling in cellular networks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the integration of AI into wireless networks and proposes a DRL-based solution for scheduling. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates how expert knowledge can help with AI module in cellular networks, which is related to control and optimization of systems. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers link adaptation and feedback mechanisms in the simulation platform, which are related to information theory in communication systems.
